  "explanation": "The defendant is a first-time offender who committed a non-violent financial crime involving $25,000, with partial restitution already made. While embezzlement is a serious breach of trust, the sentencing guidelines for a non-violent, first-time white-collar crime typically trend toward shorter periods of incarceration, community service, and full restitution. The outburst from the spectator is legally irrelevant and was excluded from consideration in determining the proportionality of the sentence. Considering the specific amount and the mitigating factor of partial restitution, six months is an appropriate term of incarceration relative to the severity of the offense.",
